narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I would have liked more discussion and not just presentations by students that take the whole class... every single class... I understand that the reading responses were a way to express our thoughts but I would have loved to discuss the topics with my classmates, TA, and professor.
Insights you will get nowhere else
The syllabus is great and the professor offers incredible insights. I just wish that the class could be more discussion based.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Professor Zedillo is a gem. Great way to finish off Yale
Great course and Zedillo is a wonderful professor
Yes. I think this seminar is a great source to learn about Latin American economies. Professor Zedillo brings with him extraordinary experience and insights into the very issues we learn in class.

Yes, but be prepared to work on the reading responses due every week. The professor expects that you'll engage with the readings that he assigns in crafting your reading responses, and they are graded as mini-essays!
